The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Vadodara, Aug. 9: National Thermal Power Corporation Ltd is likely to set up power plants in Nigeria and Sri Lanka. A proposal is being pursued with the Federal Government of Nigeria for setting up coal and gas-based power plants in the country and sourcing of gas for NTPCs units in India, NTPC chairman and managing director R.S. Sharma said.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: The Supreme Court has upheld the conviction of former Uco Bank CMD K. Margabandhu and former general manager Ramaiya Venkatkrishnan in the 1992 securities scam case. Each of them will have to pay a fine of Rs 1 lakh. However, it said the period of imprisonment undergone would be deducted from the sentence.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: The government is likely to come up with an index in the next six months to track price variation in the services sector such as telecom and railways. The index is expected to be similar to the indices for wholesale price or consumer price.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: Mahindra Satyam today said the government should not assess the income tax liability of the IT firm before the restatement of financial accounts is completed.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: A delegation of the Federation of Indian Airlines  the apex industry body of scheduled carriers  will meet civil aviation minister Praful Patel tomorrow to press for lower taxes on jet fuel and reduced airport charges.                                                                                                                           
